<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Punjab Earthquake Disaster History</title>

    <style>
        body {
            margin: 0;
            font-family: "Segoe UI", Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: #f6f8f5;
            color: #333;
            display: flex;
        }

        /* Sidebar */
        .sidebar {
            width: 220px;
            background-color: #eef3ed;
            padding: 25px;
            border-right: 3px solid #0f9d58;   /* Updated */
            height: 100vh;
            position: fixed;
            top: 0;
            left: 0;
            box-sizing: border-box;
            box-shadow: 2px 0 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
        }

        .sidebar h3 {
            color: #0b6e3f; /* darker match */
            font-size: 1.3rem;
            margin-bottom: 15px;
            font-weight: bold;
        }

        .sidebar a {
            text-decoration: none;
            color: #222;
            display: block;
            margin: 12px 0;
            padding: 10px 12px;
            font-size: 1.05rem;
            border-radius: 6px;
            transition: 0.3s;
        }

        .sidebar a:hover {
            background-color: #c8f3dc;   /* soft green hover */
            border-left: 5px solid #0f9d58; /* Updated */
            padding-left: 18px;
        }

        /* Main content */
        .main-content {
            margin-left: 0px;
            padding: 20px 40px;
            flex: 1;
            animation: fadeIn 0.8s ease-in-out;
        }

        @keyframes fadeIn {
            from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(10px); }
            to { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
        }

        /* Header */
        header {
            background-color: #0f9d58; /* Updated */
            color: white;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 25px 10px;
            font-size: 32px;
            font-weight: bold;
            letter-spacing: 1px;
            position: relative;
            border-radius: 10px;
            margin-bottom: 25px;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.15);
        }

        /* Flags */
        header::after {
            content: '';
            position: absolute;
            top: 15px;
            width: 65px;
            height: 45px;
            background-image: url('https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/4/41/Flag_of_India.svg');
            background-size: cover;
        }
        header::after { right: 15px; }

        /* Headings */
        h2 {
            color: #0b6e3f;  /* Updated */
            border-left: 6px solid #0f9d58; /* Updated */
            padding-left: 12px;
            margin-top: 25px;
            font-size: 1.8rem;
        }

        /* Year Blocks */
        .year-block {
            background: #d9f5e6;  /* lighter green backdrop */
            padding: 18px 20px;
            border-left: 5px solid #0f9d58; /* Updated */
            margin-bottom: 18px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            box-shadow: 0 2px 7px rgba(0,0,0,0.08);
            transition: transform 0.2s;
        }

        .year-block:hover {
            transform: translateY(-3px);
        }

        .year-block h3 {
            margin: 0;
            color: #0b6e3f; /* Updated heading color */
            font-size: 1.3rem;
            margin-bottom: 8px;
        }

        .year-block p {
            line-height: 1.65;
            font-size: 1.05rem;
        }

        /* Paragraphs */
        .main-content p {
            font-size: 1.1rem;
            background: #ffffff;
            padding: 10px 18px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            border-left: 4px solid #0f9d58; /* Updated */
            box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.05);
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }

    </style>
</head>

<body>

<div class="main-content">

    <header>
         Earthquake Disaster History
    </header>

    <p>
        Punjab occasionally experiences mild tremors due to seismic activity in northern India, especially Himachal
        Pradesh and Kashmir regions. Although not a high-risk seismic zone, several events over the years have influenced
        state preparedness and awareness.
    </p>

    <h2>Earthquake Disaster Timeline</h2>

    <div class="year-block">
        <h3>1998 – Himachal Pradesh Earthquake Tremors</h3>
        <p>
            • Tremors felt across Hoshiarpur, Pathankot, and Gurdaspur.<br>
            • Minor structural cracks in older residential buildings.<br>
            • Triggered demand for public awareness on earthquake safety.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="year-block">
        <h3>2005 – Kashmir Earthquake Aftershocks</h3>
        <p>
            • Noticeable shaking reported across Punjab.<br>
            • Authorities reviewed emergency response strategies.<br>
            • First major earthquake drill conducted in schools and hospitals.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="year-block">
        <h3>2011 – Minor Northern Shocks</h3>
        <p>
            • Tremors felt for a few seconds across northern Punjab.<br>
            • No major damage, but monitoring systems were strengthened.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="year-block">
        <h3>2015 – Statewide Seismic Safety Review</h3>
        <p>
            • Continuous activity in northern India prompted audits of key buildings.<br>
            • New construction guidelines introduced for government structures.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="year-block">
        <h3>2020 – Border District Tremors</h3>
        <p>
            • Mild earthquakes sensed in Gurdaspur and Pathankot.<br>
            • NDRF and SDMA increased public training and awareness campaigns.
        </p>
    </div>

    <h2>Summary</h2>
    <p>
        Though Punjab is relatively safe from major earthquakes, past events have helped the state improve infrastructure,
        readiness drills, monitoring systems, and seismic safety standards. Continuous awareness and preparedness remain
        essential for reducing risks in the future.
    </p>

</div>

</body>
</html>